<content type="application/x.deki0805+xml" title="vbox"><body xmlns:eval="http://mindtouch.com/2007/dekiscript"><div class="noinclude"><span class="script">template.XULRefElem()</span></div> <p>A container element which can contain any number of child elements. This is equivalent to the <code><span class="script">template.XULElem("box")</span></code> element, except it defaults to vertical orientation.
</p><p>More information is available in the <a href="en/XUL_Tutorial/The_Box_Model">XUL tutorial</a>.
</p>
<h3 name="Example"> Example </h3>
<pre>
&lt;!-- Two labels at bottom --&gt;
&lt;vbox&gt;
  &lt;spacer flex="1"/&gt;
  &lt;label value="One"/&gt;
  &lt;label value="Two"/&gt;
&lt;/vbox&gt;
</pre>
